> "His face is telling me nothing. I've seen Harris broad and full of laughter. Today he is tight, as much part of the military machine as the device in Hut 5.\n" [Continue]
> "\"We need that component,\" he says.\n" [Choices: "The stolen component..." (0), "Shrug" (1) -> 0]
> "The reel went missing from the Bombe this afternoon. The four of us were in the Hut, working on the latest German intercept. The results were garbage. It was Russell who found the gap in the plugboard.\n" [Continue]
> "Any of us could have taken it; and no one else would have known its worth.\n" [Choices: "Panic" (0), "Calculate" (1), "Deny" (2) -> 0]
> "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n" [Continue]
> "\"So. Do you have it?\" Harris is wasting no time: Bletchley is his watch. \"Do you know where it is?\"\n" [Choices: "Yes" (0), "No" (1), "Lie" (2), "Evade" (3) -> 0]
> "\"I do.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Harris smiles with satisfaction, as if your willingness to talk was somehow his doing.\n" [Continue]
> "\"I see.\"\n" [Continue]
> "There's a long pause, like the delay between feeding a line of cypher into the Bombe and waiting for its valves to warm up enough to begin processing.\n" [Continue]
> "\"You want to explain that?\"\n" [Choices: "Explain" (0), "Say nothing" (1) -> 1]
> "I fold my arms, intended firmly to say nothing. But somehow, watching Harris' face, I cannot bring myself to do it. I want to confess. I want to tell him everything I can, to explain myself to him, to earn his forgiveness. The sensation is so strong my will is powerless in the face of it.\n" [Continue]
> "Something is wrong with me, I am sure of it. There is a strange, bitter flavour on my tongue. I taste it as words start to form.\n" [Continue]
> "\"I've done things,\" I begin. \"Things I didn't want to do. I tried not to. But in the end, it felt like cutting off my own arm to resist.\"\n" [Continue]
